# Cloudflare Pages _headers — explicit cache directives on the SPA root.
#
# Defense layer for stale-chunk recovery. The blank-screen bug fixed via
# SvelteKit version polling (see svelte.config.js) relies on the browser
# eventually fetching a fresh index.html — pin no-long-cache on the SPA
# entry so the new bundle hashes propagate as soon as a deploy lands.
# Pages already sends `cache-control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate`
# on `/` by default; this file makes the contract explicit so a future
# Pages-side default change cannot silently regress the recovery path.
/index.html
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate

/
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=0, must-revalidate
